It's not the language that's verbose, it's the Cocoa libraries.<p>Instead of this:<p><pre><code>  NSString *s2 = [s1 stringByAddingPercentEscapesUsingEncoding:NSUTF8Encoding];
</code></pre>
You could easily have:<p><pre><code>  NSString *s2 = [s1 percentEscapes:UTF8];
</code></pre>
(I like the first way better, though. It reads like an English sentence, and you know exactly what the arguments are.)<p>EDIT: formatting.
